  <description type="morphology">Shrubs, 1–2(–4) m. Stems 1–50, solitary or in colonies. Leaves: petiole (7–)11.9–19.1(–27) mm; blade orbiculate to oval, (14–)26–37(–50) × (18–)23–36(–43) mm, base usually cordate to truncate, sometimes ± cuneate, apex rounded or subtruncate, surfaces glabrous. Inflorescences (6 or)7–9(–12)-flowered, (24–)29–40(–47) mm. Pedicels proximalmost (8–)10–20(–27) mm. Flowers: sepals (2.7–)3.2–4(–4.5) mm; petals obovate to elliptic, (9–)10.9–11.5(–12.6) × (3–)3.8–5.2(–5.9) mm; ovary apex glabrous (or sparsely hairy with a ring of hairs at base of styles). Pomes 8–9 mm diam. 2n = 4x.</description>
